===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{cattag|Military}} A [[cannon]] with relatively long [[barrel]], operating with relatively low angle of fire, and having a high [[muzzle]] [[velocity]]. JP 1-02.
# {{cattag|Military}} A cannon with tube length 30 [[caliber]]s or more. See also: [[howitzer]]; [[mortar]]. JP 1-02.
# A very portable, short weapon, for hand use; a bullet or projectile firing [[weapon]].
# A less portable, long weapon; a bullet or projectile firing weapon; a [[rifle]], either manual, [[automatic]] or [[semi-automatic]].
#:This is my rifle, this is my gun. One is for fighting, one is for fun. (U.S. military chant, used to make recruits memorize that the only correct term for a soldier's firearm is 'rifle', not some 'gun'.)
# {{cattag|surfing}} A long [[surfboard]] designed for [[surfing]] big [[wave]]s (not the same as a [[longboard]], a gun has a pointed nose and is generally a little narrower).
#: 2000: ''by the winter of 1962, the Brewer Surfboards Hawaii '''gun''' was the most in-demand big-wave equipment on the North Shore.'' &mdash; Drew Kampion at surfline.com [http://www.surfline.com/surfaz/surfaz.cfm?id=766]

